Sentencas: The characteristics of solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) cathodes, prepared by infiltration of La0.8Sr0.2FeO3-delta (LSF) into porous yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) scaffolds, were evaluated by studying the effect of p(O-2) and of Al2O3 overlayers deposited by Atomic Layer Deposition (ALD) on impedance spectra at 873 and 973 K.
Titulo: An Investigation of Oxygen Reduction Kinetics in LSF Electrodes

Sentencas: The electrode resistance of LSF-YSZ composites calcined at 1123 K was dominated by high-frequency processes that show a relatively weak p(O-2) dependence of -0.2 at 973 K.
